{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/62/comments/79147593.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo:52be49ec7f2f..14a619f929f7?path=src%2FSimulationRunner.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/62/_/diff#comment-79147593"}}, "parent": {"id": 79146708, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/62/comments/79146708.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/62/_/diff#comment-79146708"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 62, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/62.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/62"}}, "title": "Erase entity [Ready for review]"}, "content": {"raw": "A System can't delete entities unless we expand how systems work and are updated.\n\nErasing an entity is not equal to erasing a model, which would erase joints and child links for example.\n\nThe asynchronous nature of deletion is something we can't handle gracefully right now. We'd have to have long running services, like actions.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>A System can't delete entities unless we expand how systems work and are updated.</p>\n<p>Erasing an entity is not equal to erasing a model, which would erase joints and child links for example.</p>\n<p>The asynchronous nature of deletion is something we can't handle gracefully right now. We'd have to have long running services, like actions.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-10-15T22:55:33.087879+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b